File: The Weather Service has now downgraded the South Western parts of the KwaZulu-Natal to alert level two. The North has also been downgraded to level four. eNCA/Estelle Bronkhorst KWAZULU-NATAL -Â KwaZulu-Natal COGTA MEC, Sihle Zikalala is urging communities to be vigilant amid severe weather warnings. This as heavy rains continue to disrupt large parts of the province. An 8-year-old has drowned in Pietermaritzburg. There's also reports of power outages as a result of persistent rains. The Weather Service has now downgraded the South Western parts of the KwaZulu-Natal to alert level two. The North has also been downgraded to level four.